cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks such as image classification and face detection, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel pooling operator based on Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs), which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, indicating that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the computational complexity and efficiency of the proposed method, which could place it in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of a microcontroller with limited RAM, which could suggest that it belongs to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category, which deals with multimedia systems and applications.
